# Code Changes

- Change only what the task requires — no drive-by refactors or unrelated edits.
- Read surrounding code before writing; match its naming, types, and abstractions.
- Do not add tests unless the user asks or they cover real behavior worth asserting.
- Do not create markdown files the user did not ask for.
- Do not add comments that restate what the code already says — only non-obvious logic.
